<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-04T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-04T18:00:00-05:00" n="1592" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1592">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.62/94.</note>
                            <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-04T18:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">August 4, 1914, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Your August 2, 9 p.m. Department is to-day telegraphing Vice Consul
                                Silliman at Saltillo to advise General Carranza to exercise clemency
                                in the case of the two Mexican refugees on board <hi rend="italic">Antonina</hi>.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>